Nominated Jubilee Senator Paul Njoroge has said he is opposed to the amendments to the election laws. He differed with his colleagues on Tuesday, saying amending the laws is part of a plan to rig the August 8 general election.Njoroge accused DP William Ruto of orchestrating it. Senate Speaker Ekwee Ethuro has summoned senators on Wednesday for a special sitting to discuss the amendments.Last week, Jubilee and Cord MPs clashed in the National Assembly before the amendments were hurriedly passed. Njoroge termed the move illegal, saying no amendment should be carried before six months. He urged President Uhuru Kenyatta not to assent.